---
title: "Recollections and Mementos of G. A. Pfeiffer"
year: 1990
abstract: >
  This is a personal reminiscence about my early family association with "Uncle Gus" Pfeiffer, and a list of the mementos of it which still survive. The Pfeiffer Foundation presumably has already a large collection of Gus Pfeiffer mementos. However, in view of my present age (68) and since none of my surviving relatives and acquaintances would understand what they mean, I would be glad to donate any of mine that it wants to the Pfeiffer Foundation, which can give them a better future home than I can.
author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
